<subSubSection id="C7B77338D535F02D5447588F48D947A2" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8895512B85897B1CD6E6E143A84E89CF" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F1285AC6A9E42A518CFB7F3D3D852CCA" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">
The new species 
<taxonomicName id="93CA16A719F322269C90ADAFEA637EF5" authorityName="Acev. - Rodr. &amp; S. W. Brewer" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Spathelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spathelia belizensis" order="Sapindales" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="belizensis">
<emphasis id="4DAD0FD982204367AB0EA2DF8A52DE26" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Spathelia belizensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seems to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="7E9D7A1CCC73E6F0C66454F29D49DE95" authorityName="P Wilson" authorityYear="1911" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Spathelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spathelia brittonii" order="Sapindales" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brittonii">
<emphasis id="CFB9AAC422E0EF5955F8F51EF85ED1F4" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Spathelia brittonii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
P. Wilson due to their similar adult height, large leaves, and indument of stellate and simple hairs. 
<taxonomicName id="20E8A1A21160207DFCF7BA742A188BAC" authorityName="Acev. - Rodr. &amp; S. W. Brewer" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Spathelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spathelia belizensis" order="Sapindales" pageId="1" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="belizensis">
<emphasis id="0B05169E5B5B2AE450FCA0BCF850B4D2" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="146">Spathelia belizensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the latter by having leaves with 75-91 leaflets with crenate margins, unequal sepals, white petals, and fruits with ovate outline and obtuse apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
